# Review & Comparison Article Accuracy

When writing or publishing reviews/comparisons for AIGC Room:

## Must NOT fabricate

- Fake hands-on tests ("We ran 40 benchmarks", "We audited 200 listings") unless actually done and documented
- Precise scores (9.2/10), win rates (32/40), or timing (38 min) without real measured data
- Specific pricing as fact without linking to official pricing pages — use "approx." + "verify on site"
- Feature claims — confirm against official docs/product pages

## Allowed

- **Editor's pick** recommendations with clear reasoning (no fake numeric scores)
- Qualitative comparisons ("generally better for X") based on public feature lists
- Affiliate disclosure on every monetized article
- "Last checked: Month Year" for pricing/features with link to official source

## Required in every comparison article

1. Affiliate disclosure block
2. Line: verify pricing/features on official sites before buying
3. Methodology note: editorial comparison based on public docs + hands-on where stated — not lab benchmarks unless we ran them
4. FAQ answers must not invent policy (Amazon rules → link Seller Central; tool limits → link vendor)

## Tone

Honest > hype. Readers trust us more than fake precision. Wrong Amazon compliance advice can harm sellers — cite official policy, avoid made-up percentages.
